    "department": "Corporate",
    "description": "LIFE AT UIPATH\n\nThe people at UiPath believe in the transformative power of automation to change how the world works. We’re committed to creating category-leading enterprise software that unleashes that power.\n\nTo make that happen, we need people who are curious, self-propelled, generous, and genuine. People who love being part of a fast-moving, fast-thinking growth company. And people who care—about each other, about UiPath, and about our larger purpose.\n\nCould that be you?\n\n\nYOUR MISSION\n\nYou as a Principal Data Engineer will shape and evolve our modern data platform. This is a senior individual contributor role with high strategic impact, strong architectural ownership, and clear expectations around leadership influence, initiative, and autonomous execution.\nOur data ecosystem is built on Microsoft Fabric, and we expect this role to drive best practices, scalability, and long-term platform evolution. While prior Fabric experience is not mandatory, strong experience in comparable modern cloud data platforms is essential.\nThis role goes beyond implementation—it requires someone who challenges the status quo, drives technical direction, and elevates the engineering bar across the team.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO AT UIPATH\n\n - Own and evolve the architecture of our modern data platform (Fabric-based lakehouse environment)\n\n - Lead complex, cross-functional data initiatives end-to-end with minimal oversight\n\n - Define and enforce engineering standards, modeling best practices, and performance optimization\n\n - Design and optimize scalable ELT pipelines and dimensional data models\n\n - Drive platform reliability, governance, and cost-performance balance\n\n - Evaluate and introduce new tools and architectural improvements\n\n - Act as a technical leader and mentor within the data organization\n\n - Partner with Finance, Sales, and other stakeholders to translate business strategy into scalable data solutions\n   \n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL BRING TO THE TEAM\n\nCore Requirements:\n-7+ years of experience in data engineering / data platform roles\n- Expert-level SQL skills (mandatory) — advanced transformations, optimization, scalable modeling\n-Good working knowledge of Python and/or PySpark\n- Proven experience designing and operating modern cloud-based data platforms\n(e.g., Fabric, Databricks, Snowflake, Synapse, Redshift, BigQuery, etc.)\n- Strong understanding of lakehouse architecture and ELT patterns\n- Experience building scalable dimensional models and enterprise-grade data solutions\n- Experience integrating complex enterprise systems (ERP, CRM, HRIS, etc.)\n\n\nPlatform Context:\n\n- We currently operate on Microsoft Fabric (Lakehouse, Pipelines, Notebooks, Data Warehouse)\n- Direct Fabric experience is a plus — but experience in similar modern distributed/cloud data platforms is expected, along with the ability to quickly adapt and lead within Fabric\n\n\nLeadership Expectations:\n\n-High degree of ownership and accountability\n\n- Comfortable making architectural decisions in ambiguous environments\n\n- Proactive in identifying risks and improvement opportunities\n\n- Ability to influence technical direction without formal authority\n\n- Strong mentoring capability and engineering mindset\n\n- Strategic thinking combined with hands-on execution\n\n\nWhat Success Looks Like\n\n - A scalable, reliable, and future-proof data platform\n\n - Elevated engineering standards and architectural clarity\n\n - High-impact initiatives delivered with autonomy\n\n - A stronger data engineering culture driven by your influence\n   \n   #LI-CS1\n\nMaybe you don’t tick all the boxes above—but still think you’d be great for the job? Go ahead, apply anyway. Please. Because we know that experience comes in all shapes and sizes—and passion can’t be learned.\n\nMany of our roles allow for flexibility in when and where work gets done. Depending on the needs of the business and the role, the number of hybrid, office-based, and remote workers will vary from team to team. Applications are assessed on a rolling basis and there is no fixed deadline for this requisition. The application window may change depending on the volume of applications received or may close immediately if a qualified candidate is selected.\n\nWe value a range of diverse backgrounds, experiences and ideas. We pride ourselves on our diversity and inclusive workplace that provides equal opportunities to all persons regardless of age, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, and expression, national origin, disability, neurodiversity, military and/or veteran status, or any other protected classes. Additionally, UiPath provides reasonable accommodations for candidates on request and respects applicants' privacy rights. To review these and other legal disclosures, visit our privacy policy https://www.uipath.com/legal/trust-and-security/privacy-policy.",
